    "last_activity_date" : 1286941754,
    "creation_date" : 1286941754,
    "answer_id" : 3920639,
    "question_id" : 3920602,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>You can simply get your answer from ArrayList <a href=\"http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/ArrayList.html#get%28int%29\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">API</a> doc. </p>\n\n<p>Please always refer API documentation .. it helps </p>\n\n<p>Your call will looklike following :</p>\n\n<pre><code>mainList.get(3);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Here is simple tutorial for understanding ArrayList with Basics :) :</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.javadeveloper.co.in/java/java-arraylist-tutorial.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">http://www.javadeveloper.co.in/java/java-arraylist-tutorial.html</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 74042,
      "reputation" : 13508,
      "user_id" : 212952,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c9ca93d5233a833392cd5a2eac860ab3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Tomas Narros",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/212952/tomas-narros"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 262,
    "last_activity_date" : 1418351244,
    "last_edit_date" : 1418351244,
    "creation_date" : 1286980092,
    "answer_id" : 3924759,
    "question_id" : 3920602,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>As many have already told you:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mainList.get(3);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Be sure to check the <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/ArrayList.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">ArrayList Javadoc</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Also, be careful with the arrays indices: in Java, the first element is at index <code>0</code>. So if you are trying to get the third element, your solution would be <code>mainList.get(2);</code></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2765197,
